@OZAMA Possibly you need to first refresh the prerequisites ie OOP (C#) and SQL (RDBMS). Also if your're a beginner and you really want to learn ASP .NET, I'd suggest a proper course which would be a lot longer than 1 hour tho.

This is a crash course, typically meant for professionals looking to relearn or quickly get the hang of the basics so they can start working on projects.

Since you're 18, you should take it slow and solidify your fundamentals alongside developing personal projects as that's what you need to put on your CV.
